<br>
While not an exclusive guild by any means Asylum's Gate is selective in its recruiting practices and does require that potential candidates prove their worthiness to be considered for membership by completing the following steps:<br>
<br>
1 - READ the Guild Charter and bi-laws listed in this forum and consider you reason for wanting to join the Gate and determine if those reasons are in line with the principles and guidelines the Gate is founded upon.<br>
<br>
2 - Seek out, in game, one of the officers listed in the &quot;Officers and High Council Members&quot; string of this forum and make your intentions known (note you will not be given a guild tag at this point).<br>
<br>
3 - If deemed worthy of consideration for membership return to this message board and using the password provided to you by the officer, post the following in the &quot;Membership Petitions&quot; Forum:<br>
<br>
-Your primary characters class, level and other <br>
pertinent information<br>
<br>
-An email address you can be reached through<br>
<br>
-The name of the officer that disclosed <br>
the &quot;Membership petitions&quot; password to you<br>
<br>
-Where you first heard about Asylum's Gate<br>
<br>
-Why you wish to be considered for membership<br>
<br>
-What you feel you bring to the guild<br>
<br>
-Any thing else you wish to say about yourself <br>
and your worthiness to be considered for<br>
membership.<br>
<br>
4 - Once you have posted you have 2 weeks to actively seek out members of Asylum's Gate and make every effort to group with and get to know as many members as possible. It is also your responsibility during this period to find an officer that is willing to sponsor you as an official tagged candidate for membership (this does NOT have to be the same officer that directed you to the &quot;Membership Petitions forum).<br>
<br>
5 - After two weeks from your initial post in the &quot;Membership Petitions&quot; forum your sponsor is then allowed, at his/her discretion, to give you a guild tag thus starting the second phase of you application for full membership.<br>
<br>
6 - Once tagged you will be sent a new recruit letter outlining the guild, its policies and what will be required of you in this phase of recruitment. Note that during this phase you will have most all of the rights and privileges of the full members. It is not our intent to make you jump through hoops during this period or &quot;pay your dues&quot; as some guilds require, the purpose of this phase is merely to allow you to get to know the general membership and allow them to get to know you. After a period of no less than one month has passed from being tagged the officers of Asylum's Gate will vote on your full membership. <br>
<br>
7 - Once the officers have voted the decision is final. Providing the vote is affirmative there will be much celebration and general debauchery as we welcome you as a full member of the greatest guild on Norrath. (then we will drag you blindfolded to the middle of Kithcor at midnight and leave you naked to find your way back to Freeport by dawn  ....no wait, sorry old fraternity flashback lol)<br>
<br>
If after reading all this and studying the charter and bi-laws you decide to continue your pursuance of membership in Asylum's Gate...God speed and good luck on the most important and rewarding quest you will ever undertake. I hope some day to welcome you as a full member of the Gate.<br>
<br>
LONG LIVE THE GATE!!!!!!<br>
